message.content:
cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with scheduling strategies in wireless networks to improve quality of experience (QoE) of users. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel maximum-weight-type scheduling policy that maximizes system throughput. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper introduces a new quantity, the time-since-last-service (TSLS), to track the service regularity of links. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper proposes a scheduling policy that considers the regular interservice times for all links, which can be seen as a multiagent system. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper aims to improve the quality of experience (QoE) of users by providing regular service guarantees, which can be seen as a performance metric.
